Its alleged a man offered to hire a taxi for them to the Khutsong playgrounds but then took them to the Oberholzer Train Station. JOHANNESBURG - Police have confirmed that 15 children who went missing after a soccer match in Khutsong this past weekend are now safe and have been returned to their parents. Its alleged a man offered to hire a taxi for the children to the Khutsong south playgrounds but then took them to the Oberholzer Train Station. Police say all the children found at the train station have been returned to their parents. The police's Lungelo Dlamini said, I think the information we got from the parents was not accurate and we established that the children who were left at the park station have all been reunited with their parents but we re still continuing with the case. 